description: This walk combines trails through Brisbane Water National Park and Rumbalara and Katandra Reserves with an optional detour along the Brisbane Water Cycleway.

markers.description: Get the train to Woy Woy using transportnsw.info.
From the station exit follow Railway St left past the bus stops to the pedestrian crossing.
Cross Brisbane Water Dr and continue left past past the pub.
Cross the Boulevarde and continue straight along Brisbane Water Dr on the shared path.
One of the few remaining Krillz not pillz graffiti dotted around Central Coast.
markers.title: A Whale of a Time
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: Cross Spike Milligan Bridge and continue on the shaed path along Brisbane Water Dr.
-1hTo avoid climbing the steep hill, keep following the shared path along Brisbane Water Dr.
Follow the directions along the waterfront path to Gosford.
There is a toilet block in Koolewong Waterfront Reserve after the boat ramp.
From Tascott Station keep following the shared path along Brisbane Water Dr.
At the bus stop follow the shared path to the right down the ramp.
Follow the shared path along the fence line.
From the end of the path follow Kurrawa Ave straight on.
After the station follow Kurrawa Ave along the railway line to Goodayway Reserve.
From the carpark follow the steps up into the picnic area.
There is a toilet block at the far end of the picnic area.
After passing through the picnic area use the railway underpass on the left.
After crossing Spike Milligan Bridge, follow the steps under the bridge.
Follow the footpath under the bridge to the right.
From the bridge follow the firetrail to the right.
The firetrail is steep and covered in loose rocks. Do not take this route if it looks too dangerous.
Pass the gate and follow the firetrail uphill.
Follow the short section of steps along the left side of the trail.
Pass the gate at the top of the climb and follow the firetrail past the radio towers.
At the intersection follow Koolewong Firetrail to the right.
There are several incidental lookouts along the left and right side of the trail.
The top of the hairpin bend is an incidental lookout across Koolewong.
At the intersection follow the Corrumbine Creek Firetrail to the right.
At the split with the powerline service trail, follow Corrumbine Creek Firetrail to the left.
From the contrete barriers continue following Corrumbine Creek Firetrail downhill.
Cross the creek and continue around the corner.
Follow the concrete ramp uphill.
From the top of the ramp continue straight on Corrumbine Creek Firetrail.
At the intersection with the concrete barriers follow Milyerra Rd Firetrail to the right.
Follow the concrete ramp down the steep hairpin bend.
At the intersection follow the firetrail left to a turning loop.
From the corner of the turning loop follow the bush trail along the ridge.
Follow the bush trail to the trailhead on the right side of the houses.
Follow the steps between houses down to Penang St.
From the steps follow Penang St down hill.
At the intersection follow Brisbane Water Dr to the left.
At the pedestrian crossing near the bus stop cross Brisbane Water Dr and continue left.
At the intersection follow Collar Rd to the right.
At the intersection follow Welwyn Grove to the right.
From railway underpass follow the shared bike path left to Gosford.
Follow the shared path along the sports fields at Fagan Park
There is a toilet block at the end of the sports fields.
From the sports fields follow the shared path along the shorefront.
Cross the bridge over Coorumbine Creek and continue on the shared path on the other side.
At the intersection follow the sign to Gosford to the right.
From the end of the path follow Yallambee Ave to the right past Bunnings.
At the intersection cross the Central Coast Highway at the traffic lights and continue right.
Cross the bridge over Narara Creek and continue along the Central Coast Highway.
At the intersection cross Racecourse Rd at the traffic lights and continue straight on Central Coast Highway.
Before the overpass follow the offramp to the left.
At the bottom of the ramp follow Pacific Hwy to the left.
After the roundabout cross the Pacific Hwy at the pedestrian crossing and continue left.
Follow the footpath past the station carpark to the station entrance.
Get the train to/from Gosford using transportnsw.info.
Exit the station on the Burns Cres side.
From the station follow Burns Cres to the right.
At the intersection follow Mann St to the right.
At the intersection follow the sign to Rumbalara Reserve to the left down Donnison St.
Cross at the traffic lights and continue straight on Donnison St.
Continue straight on narrower section of Donnison St.
At the corner of Donnison St enter the carpark of Rumbalara Reserve to the left.
From the carpark follow the steps up the park map.
From the park map follow the sign left to Iron Bark Loop.
Follow the park sign to Nurrunga Picnic Area.
Follow the steps up the hill to the right.
At the split follow the park sign to the picnic area.
From the top of the steps follow the Iconbark Loop left to Nurrunga Picnic Area.
Follow the Ironbark Loop around the picnic area.
From the picnic area continue following the signs along the Ironbark Loop.
From the intersection follow the paved Dolly Ave to the left.
Follow Dolly Ave to Yaruga Picnic Area.
There is a toilet block at the carpark.
There is a lookout at the picnic area to the right of Dolly Ave.
From Yaruga Picnic Area follow Dolly Ave to the water tank.
At the water tank continue following Dolly Ave to the right.
At the trailhead follow the sign to Muoat Walk to the left.
The fourth explorer statue requires some exploring.
markers.title: The Solitary Explorer
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: Follow the stone steps down the hairpin and continue following Mouat Walk.
At the split choose either direction to follow the Mouat Walk.
At the gate follow the trail right along the fence line.
Follow either the bushtrail sections or the easier firetail along Mouat Walk.
From the gated intersection continue straight on the paved section of Mouat Walk.
Either follow the bushtrail on the right or keep following the paved road.
Pass the gate and continue straight on Toomeys Rd.
+100m Optionally enter the carpark of Katandra Reserve on the right.
There is a lookout platform at the picnic area.
There is a toilet block at the picnic area.
From Katandra Reserve continue straight along Atkinson Rd.
At the split follow Mount Elliot Pl to the left.
At the end of Mount Elliot Pl pass the gate and continue straight along the firetrail.
At the top of the hill follow the sign right to Taylor Rd.
Pass the fence and follow Taylor Rd to the right.
At the intersection follow The Ridgeway to the left.
Cross the Pacific Hwy at the traffic lights to the station entrance.
Plan your return trip from Lisarow at transportnsw.info.
